and that a momentary conflict however desperate, even for precarious liberty, is better than a slow and gradual descent, however peaceful, into con∣firmed slavery Malo periculosam libertatem quam quietum servitium.. Be this granted; in any case the preservation of liberty, depends on the precise de∣termination of the limits, between the privileges of the people, and the powers of government.
